                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51 Sa 6/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Earle Bailie</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1925.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your visit to the Department on
                    August 19 [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>], during which you inquired whether the
                    Department would have any objection to a projected loan by your firm to the
                    Paulista Institute for the Permanent Defense of Coffee of São Paulo, I beg to
                    say in reply that in the light of the information before it, the Department
                    cannot view this financing with favor.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph C. Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Under Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
